glosses: To become thin, to reduce in width or thickness.
To become more fluid, more inviscid, to lose viscosity.

etymology:
Inherited from Ottoman Turkish اینجلمك (incelmek), from اینجه (ince), equivalent to
ince (“thin”) + -l (verb-forming suffix) + -mak. Cognates with Azerbaijani incəlmək, Turkmen inçelmek, Uzbek ingichkalashmoq.
